oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:title: Push Button One - 1955-02-03 - Part 3
oai_qdc:qualifieddc.dc:description: WSM program Push Button One, originally broadcast February 3, 1955 at 4:30 pm, part 3. Featuring announcer and DJ Dave Overton playing recorded music with news reports by Bill Williams. Dave Overton discusses topics including The Nashville Record becoming middle Tennessee's fastest growing newspaper; the Miss Nashville High contest; the filming of the Grand Old Opry at Vanderbilt Theater, February 4 at 12:30 pm; and a plug for The Waking Crew program.
